THAT HADDIE HAS A BIOLOGY TEST,

00:58.640 --> 00:59.982
YOU KNOW, AND SHE HAS NOT
EVEN STUDIED FOR IT.

01:00.020 --> 01:01.009
- UH...
- NOT ONCE.

01:01.060 --> 01:02.049
REALLY GETTING ME MAD.
SHE DOESN'T EVEN, LIKE,

01:02.090 --> 01:03.842
CARE ABOUT IT.
- WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, HEY.

01:03.890 --> 01:05.152
HEY, WE JUST HAD MORNING SEX.

01:05.200 --> 01:06.531
LIKE, FREE, BONUS,

01:06.580 --> 01:08.957
UNADULTERATED,
LIKE, PRE-KID MORNING SEX.

01:08.990 --> 01:10.469
- UH-HUH.
IT WAS NICE.

01:10.510 --> 01:11.647
- NICE?

01:11.690 --> 01:13.237
- IT WAS, UM--
IT WAS AMAZINGLY NICE.

01:13.280 --> 01:14.474
- AMAZINGLY NICE?
- MM-HMM.

01:14.520 --> 01:17.034
YEAH.
CHOP-CHOP. LET'S GO.

01:17.070 --> 01:18.344
JUST MEET ME DOWNSTAIRS.

01:18.380 --> 01:20.268
- WOULD YOU GO ALONG

01:20.320 --> 01:23.380
WITH SOMEONE LIKE ME?

01:23.420 --> 01:24.864
- NICE?

01:27.190 --> 01:29.112
- WHY DOES SCHOOL START
SO EARLY?

01:29.150 --> 01:31.254
8:30, SO DUMB.

01:31.290 --> 01:32.769
AND MONDAY.
WHY NOT START TUESDAY?

01:32.810 --> 01:35.222
- SHOULDN'T WE BE
THE ONES COMPLAINING, NO?

01:35.260 --> 01:36.773
- WELL, I'M JUST SAYING,
WHY START ON MONDAY?

01:36.820 --> 01:38.321
WHY NOT START ON TUESDAY?
- CAN YOU PULL OVER UP HERE?

01:38.370 --> 01:40.224
- WHY? WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
- JUST STOP RIGHT HERE, PLEASE.

01:40.270 --> 01:42.602
- SCHOOL'S OVER THERE.

01:42.650 --> 01:44.470
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
I'M SO EMBARRASSING

01:44.510 --> 01:46.307
THAT I CAN'T DROP YOU OFF
IN FRONT OF SCHOOL?

01:46.340 --> 01:48.228
- KIND OF.
- MORNING.

01:48.280 --> 01:50.134
both: HEY.
- HI.

01:50.170 --> 01:51.728
- DON'T MONDAYS SUCK?

01:51.760 --> 01:53.068
- I WAS JUST SAYING THAT.

01:53.110 --> 01:55.317
I LITERALLY JUST SAID THAT.
THAT'S SO WEIRD.

01:55.350 --> 01:57.830
- I'LL SEE YOU IN CLASS.
- OKAY.

01:57.870 --> 01:59.667
both: BYE.
- BYE, MR. CYR.

02:05.050 --> 02:07.154
[bell rings,
car door closes]

02:11.160 --> 02:12.604
- HI.

02:12.640 --> 02:13.846
- HEY.

02:13.890 --> 02:15.812
- WE JUST LOST OUR KEY WITNESS
IN OUR DOWNEY-SMITH TRIAL.

02:15.850 --> 02:17.647
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
- I DON'T KNOW WHAT--

02:17.680 --> 02:20.240
I GOT THE RESULTS
OF THE PATERNITY TEST.

02:20.270 --> 02:23.137
I DIDN'T REALLY WANT
TO OPEN IT BY MYSELF.

02:23.170 --> 02:25.752
- OH.
- SO MAYBE YOU COULD HELP OUT.

02:25.800 --> 02:29.008
- THAT'S REALLY SWEET,
AND IT'S ALSO KIND OF PATHETIC.

02:29.040 --> 02:31.076
HERE.
- THERE'S NO PICTURES OF ME

02:31.110 --> 02:32.338
AT ALL
IN THIS WHOLE OFFICE.

02:32.390 --> 02:34.073
YOU'RE EMBARRASSED TO HAVE ME
IN THE FAMILY?

02:34.110 --> 02:36.044
- OH, BY THE WAY,
I GOT YOU AND JABBAR

02:36.080 --> 02:38.116
INTO JOEL'S
WEDNESDAY PLAYGROUP.

02:38.150 --> 02:38.946
- WAIT, YOU GOT US IN?

02:38.980 --> 02:40.629
- THERE'S
A THREE-MONTH WAIT LIST.

02:40.670 --> 02:41.489
- FOR A PLAYGROUP?

02:41.540 --> 02:43.087
- HOW LONG IS THIS GONNA TAKE?

02:43.120 --> 02:44.849
COME ON, OPEN IT.
- WELL, I MEAN,

02:44.880 --> 02:47.223
CAN'T WE WORK UP TO IT?
- CAN YOU--OPEN IT.

02:47.270 --> 02:48.988
- WHAT ARE YOU--WHAT ARE YOU
IN SUCH A HURRY FOR?

02:49.030 --> 02:50.918
- ARE YOU AFRAID OF BEING
A FATHER OR NOT BEING A FATHER?

02:52.120 --> 02:52.120
- YES, BOTH.

02:52.170 --> 02:53.990
- YOU'RE A WIMP.
- YOU'RE A TYRANT.

02:54.030 --> 02:55.543
- MM-HMM. YOU'RE WELCOME.
OPEN IT.

03:04.560 --> 03:07.142
- [mutters]

03:07.180 --> 03:11.071
[laughs]

03:11.120 --> 03:15.568
UM...
[clears throat]

03:15.600 --> 03:18.046
HE'S MINE.

03:18.090 --> 03:21.059
I'M A FATHER.

03:21.090 --> 03:23.979
SO...

03:24.030 --> 03:25.429
SO...

03:25.480 --> 03:28.165
WHOO, WHAT--WHAT--
WHAT DO I DO NOW?

03:28.200 --> 03:32.512
I MEAN, WHAT'S THE--
I GOT TO BUY A MICROWAVE

03:32.550 --> 03:36.179
AND MOVE TO THE SUBURBS?

03:36.210 --> 03:38.132
OH, MY GOD, WE GOT TO TELL
MOM AND DAD.

03:38.180 --> 03:40.341
- YES, YOU DO.

03:40.390 --> 03:41.834
- NO, WE'LL GO TOGETHER,
YOU AND I.

03:41.870 --> 03:43.007
- GROW UP.

03:43.050 --> 03:45.621
- GROWING UP MEANS ASKING
FOR HELP, WHICH I'M DOING.

03:45.670 --> 03:47.001
- OH, THAT'S
VERY MATURE OF YOU,

03:47.050 --> 03:48.631
BUT ALSO GROW UP
AND DO IT YOURSELF.

03:48.670 --> 03:50.592
- I DON'T THINK YOU'VE READ ONE
OF THOSE BOOKS.

03:50.640 --> 03:51.800
I THINK THAT'S ALL FOR SHOW.

03:51.850 --> 03:53.499
- [chuckles]
GOOD LUCK.

03:53.540 --> 03:55.087
- YOU WANT TO FRAME THIS
FOR YOUR OFFICE?

03:55.130 --> 03:57.815
'CAUSE THIS MIGHT BE THE
DOCUMENT THAT MADE ME GROW UP.

03:57.850 --> 03:58.919
IT WOULD LOOK GREAT HERE.

03:58.960 --> 04:00.473
I MEAN, I KNOW YOU DON'T
WANT ANY PICTURES OF ME,

04:00.510 --> 04:01.886
SO MAYBE JUST THIS.

04:01.930 --> 04:03.238
- YOU'LL BE FINE!

04:05.240 --> 04:07.060
- HI, I'M GABY.

04:07.100 --> 04:08.965
- HI.

04:09.000 --> 04:10.376
- I'M MAX'S BEHAVIORAL AIDE.

04:10.420 --> 04:13.207
- OH. OH.
- OH.

04:13.250 --> 04:15.241
COME ON IN.
- THANKS.

04:20.120 --> 04:21.974
- UH...

04:22.020 --> 04:25.228
SO HOW DO YOU USUALLY START
WITH A KID LIKE MAX?

04:25.260 --> 04:27.319
- WELL, YOU GUYS TELL ME.

04:27.370 --> 04:29.531
WHAT WOULD BE MOST HELPFUL
TO GET STARTED WITH?

04:29.570 --> 04:31.640
THANK YOU.
- UH, HONEY?

04:31.680 --> 04:33.159
- HAVE A SEAT.
- WHAT, UH--WHAT DO YOU THINK?

04:33.200 --> 04:34.781
- OH, GOD, UM...

04:34.820 --> 04:36.788
[clears throat] I DON'T EVEN
KNOW WHERE TO BEGIN.

04:36.820 --> 04:37.787
THERE'S SO MANY THINGS.
I MEAN...

04:37.820 --> 04:40.027
- WELL, IF THERE WERE
A BEHAVIOR OF MAX'S

04:40.070 --> 04:43.164
YOU COULD WAVE A WAND
AND CHANGE, WHAT WOULD IT BE?

04:43.210 --> 04:45.678
- HOW MUCH WOULD A WAND
LIKE THAT COST?

04:45.730 --> 04:47.698
- OH, GOSH,
IN THE MORNINGS,

04:47.730 --> 04:50.142
IT TAKES HIM A REALLY LONG TIME
TO GET READY,

04:50.180 --> 04:51.522
LIKE, A REALLY LONG TIME.

04:51.560 --> 04:53.801
- HIS DIET--
HE'S GOT A VERY LIMITED DIET.

04:53.840 --> 04:56.183
HE'LL ONLY EAT CERTAIN THINGS,
COOKED IN CERTAIN WAYS.

04:56.220 --> 04:58.905
- RIGHT, LIKE, HE'LL ONLY EAT
EGGS IF THEY'RE COOKED

04:58.950 --> 05:00.156
IN THE ORANGE FRYING PAN.

05:00.190 --> 05:03.364
- THAT SORT OF BEHAVIOR NORMAL
FOR A KID WITH ASPERGER'S?

05:03.400 --> 05:05.083
- THE ORANGE FRYING PAN
IS NEW.

05:05.130 --> 05:08.258
- OH, IT'S WEIRD,
EVEN FOR A KID WITH ASPERGER'S.

05:08.300 --> 05:11.121
GREAT.
- AND HE HAS TAN--TANTRUMS,

05:11.170 --> 05:14.139
TEMPER TANTRUMS,
SOMETIMES SEVERE.

05:14.170 --> 05:16.206
- I DON'T KNOW
IF I'D CALL THEM SEVERE.

05:16.240 --> 05:18.105
- BITING, THE FISH TANK.
- ALL RIGHT.

05:18.140 --> 05:19.869
- THERE WAS AN INCIDENT.
- OKAY.

05:19.900 --> 05:22.004
- OKAY, TELL ME--
HOW'S HE DOING SOCIALLY?

05:22.040 --> 05:25.908
DOES HE HAVE A LOT OF FRIENDS?
DOES HE HAVE PLAYDATES?

05:25.940 --> 05:27.805
- NO.

05:27.840 --> 05:28.807
- NO?

05:28.840 --> 05:33.083
- MAX DOESN'T REALLY HAVE
ANY FRIENDS.

05:35.680 --> 05:39.320
- OKAY.
WHY DON'T WE START THERE?

05:40.340 --> 05:42.058
- THAT'S GOOD.

05:45.860 --> 05:48.829
- MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

05:48.860 --> 05:51.272
MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

05:51.310 --> 05:53.551
MAY YOU
ALWAYS DO FOR OTHERS

05:53.590 --> 05:55.967
AND LET OTHERS
DO FOR YOU

05:56.010 --> 05:58.626
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

05:58.660 --> 06:00.867
AND CLIMB
ON EVERY RUNG

06:00.910 --> 06:03.003
AND MAY YOU STAY

06:03.050 --> 06:05.598
FOREVER YOUNG

06:05.640 --> 06:08.359
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

06:08.400 --> 06:10.868
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

06:10.920 --> 06:12.808
MAY YOU
ALWAYS KNOW THE TRUTH

06:12.850 --> 06:15.398
AND SEE THE LIGHT
SURROUNDING YOU

06:15.440 --> 06:18.091
MAY YOU
ALWAYS BE COURAGEOUS

06:18.130 --> 06:20.166
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

06:20.200 --> 06:22.441
AND MAY YOU STAY

06:22.480 --> 06:24.994
FOREVER YOUNG

06:25.030 --> 06:27.032
MAY YOU STAY

06:27.070 --> 06:29.891
FOREVER YOUNG

06:33.490 --> 06:35.833
- A HORNED LIZARD CAN SQUIRT
BLOOD FROM ITS EYES.

06:35.870 --> 06:38.737
THE ARMADILLO LIZARD CAN CURL
ITSELF UP INTO A TIGHT BALL

06:38.770 --> 06:40.351
TO PROTECT ITSELF
FROM A'I'I'ACK.

06:40.400 --> 06:42.595
[alarm beeps]
THE SUNGAZER LIZARD HAS SPIKES

06:42.640 --> 06:43.538
THAT COVER ITS WHOLE BODY.

06:43.570 --> 06:45.709
AND LOTS OF LIZARDS
CAN CHANGE COLORS.

06:45.750 --> 06:47.251
- THAT'S VERY COOL, MAX.

06:47.300 --> 06:50.155
SO WE'VE BEEN DOING
WHAT YOU WANT FOR 20 MINUTES.

06:50.200 --> 06:51.713
IT'S TIME
TO TRY ONE OF MY GAMES.

06:51.750 --> 06:53.058
- NO WAY.

06:53.100 --> 06:54.749
- HEY, MAX, BE POLITE.

06:54.790 --> 06:57.190
- MAX, YOU GET TO CHOOSE
WHICHEVER ONE YOU WANT.

06:57.240 --> 06:58.377
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

06:58.410 --> 06:59.650
HE DOESN'T LIKE BOARD GAMES
AT ALL.

06:59.690 --> 07:00.725
- OKAY.
- WE'VE TRIED.

07:00.760 --> 07:01.681
- WHEN YOU MAKE A DEAL,

07:01.730 --> 07:03.823
HE HAS TO HOLD UP
HIS END OF THE BARGAIN.

07:03.870 --> 07:05.349
- OKAY.

07:05.390 --> 07:06.550
- ALL RIGHT, MAX,

07:06.590 --> 07:09.241
CHECK THIS OUT.

07:09.290 --> 07:11.861
- COOL.
- THIS IS THE DEAL, OKAY?

07:11.910 --> 07:14.458
- EVERY MINUTE YOU PLAY
ONE OF THESE GAMES,

07:14.500 --> 07:15.660
YOU GET A STICKER.

07:15.710 --> 07:18.110
I HAVE A WHOLE BUNCH OF THEM
IN MY BAG HERE, ALL RIGHT?

07:18.160 --> 07:21.391
SO YOU GET UP TO 20 STICKERS,
CASH THEM IN,

07:21.440 --> 07:22.941
YOU GET THE BOOK.

07:22.990 --> 07:24.366
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

07:24.400 --> 07:27.164
- HOW ABOUT
I GET THE BOOK FIRST,

07:27.200 --> 07:28.508
THEN WE PLAY THE GAME?

07:28.550 --> 07:30.757
- I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL,
'CAUSE YOU KNOW WHAT?

07:30.790 --> 07:34.658
I USED TO ALWAYS WANT MY DESSERT
BEFORE MY DINNER,

07:34.690 --> 07:37.796
AND IT ALWAYS TURNED OUT
I HAD TO HAVE MY VEGGIES FIRST,

07:37.830 --> 07:38.751
SO...

07:38.800 --> 07:40.552
- YEP.
- FORGET IT, THEN.

07:40.590 --> 07:42.694
- MAX!
HONEY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

07:42.730 --> 07:44.243
WHY DON'T WE GO GET A COOKIE?
- YEAH, SURE.

07:44.290 --> 07:47.009
- NO, NO, NO COOKIES.
YOU GOT TO STICK WITH THE PLAN.

07:47.050 --> 07:49.018
- OKAY.
- YOU GOTTA BE FIRM. OKAY?

07:49.050 --> 07:50.256
I'M SORRY.
- OKAY.

07:50.290 --> 07:51.564
- MAX, NO COOKIE TODAY.

07:51.600 --> 07:53.044
THE REWARD IS THE BOOK.
- I WANT THE BOOK.

07:53.090 --> 07:54.398
- SO WE'RE GONNA HAVE
TO PLAY A GAME.

07:54.430 --> 07:56.500
- NO.
I WANT THE BOOK.

07:56.540 --> 07:58.394
- WHEN HE HAS THAT TONE--
WHEN HE HAS THAT TONE,

07:58.440 --> 07:59.600
ALL BETS ARE OFF.
- IT'S OKAY.

07:59.650 --> 08:00.469
- HE'S GONNA LOSE IT.
- THAT'S OKAY.

08:00.510 --> 08:02.853
THAT'S OKAY.
- HE'S GONNA LOSE IT.

08:02.890 --> 08:04.881
- LISTEN, MAX,
NOTHING HERE IS GONNA CHANGE

08:04.930 --> 08:07.160
UNLESS YOU PUT GUACAMOLE
BACK IN THE CAGE.

08:08.590 --> 08:10.683
YOU MAKE THE CHOICE.

08:12.590 --> 08:16.037
- SORRY, GUACAMOLE.

08:18.730 --> 08:20.869
- [chuckles]
- WOW.

08:20.910 --> 08:23.595
- OKAY, LET'S PICK A GAME.

08:30.570 --> 08:32.390
- HEY.

08:32.440 --> 08:34.499
- HEY, AMBER, WHAT'S UP?

08:34.540 --> 08:37.020
- UM, I WAS
JUST WONDERING, UM...

08:37.060 --> 08:39.233
I KNOW I DIDN'T SEEM
VERY EXCITED ABOUT IT IN CLASS,

08:39.270 --> 08:42.751
BUT I WAS JUST WONDERING
IF--IF YOU WERE STILL TRYING

08:42.790 --> 08:44.132
TO GET PEOPLE TO JOIN

08:44.170 --> 08:47.958
THAT WEIRD LITERARY MAGAZINE
THINGY, THE SPECTRUM?

08:48.010 --> 08:50.319
- YEAH, YEAH.
ARE YOU INTERESTED?

08:50.350 --> 08:51.726
- I MEAN, SURE,
I GUESS,

08:51.770 --> 08:53.317
'CAUSE I HAVE
TO HAVE, LIKE,

08:53.360 --> 08:54.861
EXT RACU RRICU LAR ACTIVITIES
ANYWAY,

08:54.910 --> 08:56.116
SO I MIGHT AS WELL,
LIKE, RIGHT?

08:56.150 --> 08:58.493
- WELL, WITH A PASSIONATE PLEA
LIKE THAT,

08:58.530 --> 08:59.633
HOW CAN I SAY NO?

08:59.670 --> 09:01.399
UH, YEAH, THAT'S--
THAT'S GREAT.

09:01.430 --> 09:02.397
THAT'S FANTASTIC.

09:02.430 --> 09:05.012
SO I GUESS THE NEXT STEP
IS WE ARE FORMATTING

09:05.060 --> 09:06.709
TOMORROW AFTER SCHOOL
IN THE COMPUTER LAB.

09:06.750 --> 09:09.469
SO JUST GO THERE.
- COOL.

09:09.510 --> 09:12.161
FORMATTING IN COMPUTER LABS.

09:12.200 --> 09:14.191
AND HERE I THOUGHT
IT WOULD BE NERDY AND LAME.

09:14.240 --> 09:15.639
- [laughs]
NOT AT ALL.

09:15.690 --> 09:17.783
AND THEN WE'RE GONNA BE
FOOTNOTING AND ENDNOTING,

09:17.830 --> 09:20.446
AND IT'S GONNA BE
SO COOL.

09:20.490 --> 09:21.798
- GREAT.
- BUNCH OF COOL PEOPLE.

09:21.830 --> 09:24.242
- YOU HAVE CHALK ON YOUR...

09:24.280 --> 09:25.486
- OH.
- YEAH.

09:25.530 --> 09:29.239
- IT'S AN OCCUPATIONAL HAZARD.
I PUT IT THERE ON PURPOSE.

09:29.290 --> 09:31.667
- [chuckles]
OKAY. BYE.

09:31.700 --> 09:33.213
- ALL RIGHT, SEE YOU AROUND.
- BYE-BYE.

09:33.260 --> 09:34.909
- THANKS, AMBER.
- OKAY.

09:36.880 --> 09:37.915
- OH.

09:37.950 --> 09:40.669
THIS IS NEW.

09:40.710 --> 09:42.086
HAS IT BEEN WASHED BEFORE?

09:42.130 --> 09:44.098
- UM, I DON'T THINK SO.

09:44.130 --> 09:45.574
- WELL, I SHOULD WASH IT
SEPARATELY.

09:45.610 --> 09:46.850
- NO, YOU CAN WASH IT
WITH ALL THE OTHER TEES.

09:46.890 --> 09:48.164
- WELL, IT'S RED,
YOU KNOW.

09:48.200 --> 09:49.849
IT'LL BLEED
IF IT HASN'T BEEN WASHED BEFORE.

09:49.890 --> 09:51.403
- ALL RIGHT,
WELL, IF YOU DON'T MIND,

09:51.450 --> 09:52.542
THEN I GUESS THAT'S--
- I DON'T MIND.

09:52.590 --> 09:53.796
- BETI'ER. OKAY.

09:53.830 --> 09:56.628
- JEEZ, DIDN'T YOU DO, LIKE,
EIGHT LOADS HERE LAST WEEK?

09:56.660 --> 09:58.764
- JEEZ, GET IN A FIGHT
WITH A LEAF BLOWER?

09:58.800 --> 10:02.099
- HE JUST WANTS TO VISIT US,
AND THIS IS A GOOD EXCUSE.

10:02.150 --> 10:04.311
- HEY, I'M GLAD
YOU'RE BOTH HERE.

10:04.360 --> 10:05.736
THERE'S, UM--

10:05.770 --> 10:07.635
THERE'S SOMETHING
I'VE BEEN MEANING TO TELL YOU.

10:07.670 --> 10:09.809
S-SOMEBODY'S COME
INTO MY LIFE RECENTLY.

10:09.850 --> 10:11.772
- OH, BOY,
HERE WE GO AGAIN.

10:11.810 --> 10:13.254
- WHAT HAPPENED TO KATIE?

10:13.300 --> 10:15.052
SHE WAS A NICE GIRL, KATIE.

10:15.090 --> 10:16.705
- YEAH, NOTHING HAPPENED
TO KATIE.

10:16.750 --> 10:19.059
YOU KNOW,
THIS IS KIND OF SERIOUS.

10:19.100 --> 10:20.920
- WELL, ISN'T IT
ALWAYS SERIOUS?

10:20.960 --> 10:22.814
- FOR THE FIRST WEEK
AND A HALF.

10:22.860 --> 10:24.919
[laughs]
- [laughs mockingly]

10:24.960 --> 10:26.587
I'M SO GLAD
I CAN ENTERTAIN YOU.

10:26.620 --> 10:29.271
- OH, COME ON,
WE'RE ONLY JOKING.

10:29.310 --> 10:31.892
UH, TELL US ALL ABOUT HER.

10:36.290 --> 10:39.839
- YOU KNOW WHAT?
I GOT TO RUN TO THE STUDIO.

10:39.880 --> 10:43.839
I'LL TELL YOU
WHEN I GET THROUGH WITH THAT.

10:49.610 --> 10:52.841
[chatter]

10:55.270 --> 10:58.717
- MIDNIGHT AND THE MOON
IS WEARING MAKEUP

10:58.760 --> 11:00.990
- OH, HI.
- HI.

11:01.030 --> 11:03.419
- OOH, SORRY, HON.
SORRY.

11:03.450 --> 11:04.656
CAN YOU GRAB THEM
IN THE CORNER?

11:04.690 --> 11:06.339
HI.

11:06.380 --> 11:07.415
WHAT--WHAT'LL YOU HAVE?

11:07.450 --> 11:08.838
- UM, I'M--I'M OKAY.

11:08.870 --> 11:12.692
UM, C-CAN WE TALK
FOR JUST ONE SECOND,

11:12.740 --> 11:14.071
MAYBE, OVER HERE?

11:14.120 --> 11:15.041
- YEAH.
- SORRY.

11:15.080 --> 11:16.354
- NO, NO.
- ONE SECOND.

11:16.390 --> 11:18.597
- IS, UH...?
- VERY SHORT.

11:18.640 --> 11:20.289
- IS EVERYTHING OKAY
WITH AMBER?

11:20.330 --> 11:21.638
- UH, NO, YEAH, SHE'S FINE.

11:21.680 --> 11:23.773
NO, I'M ACT UALLY--
I'M HERE ON MY OWN BEHALF.

11:23.820 --> 11:27.404
I JUST, UH, WANTED TO...

11:27.440 --> 11:28.668
SAY--

11:28.720 --> 11:30.540
AND, UH,
THIS IS REALLY LAME

11:30.580 --> 11:32.571
AND PROBABLY EMBARRASSING
FOR ME,

11:32.620 --> 11:34.474
BUT, UM,
I'M GONNA SAY IT.

11:34.520 --> 11:37.478
I, UM...

11:37.520 --> 11:38.657
I REALLY LIKE YOU, AND--

11:38.690 --> 11:41.625
- HEY, SARAH, CAN I GET
ANOTHER DRINK DOWN HERE, PLEASE?

11:41.660 --> 11:42.866
- JUST ONE SECOND.
I'M SORRY.

11:42.900 --> 11:44.527
GO ON.
- NO, THAT'S FINE.

11:44.560 --> 11:46.699
YOU KNOW, I'VE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT YOU, UM, SINCE WE MET,

11:46.740 --> 11:48.549
AND YOU JUST--
YOU MAKE ME LAUGH,

11:48.600 --> 11:49.806
AND YOU MAKE ME FEEL GOOD.

11:49.840 --> 11:52.047
AND I JUST FEEL LIKE THERE'S...
- SARAH.

11:52.090 --> 11:54.399
- SOMETHING THAT I'LL TELL YOU
IN A SECOND...

11:54.430 --> 11:55.806
- OKAY. OKAY. THANK YOU.
- AFTER YOU TAKE CARE

11:55.850 --> 11:56.839
OF YOUR CUSTOMER.

11:56.880 --> 11:58.438
- YES, YES.
ANOTHER ONE?

11:58.470 --> 11:59.505
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.
- YEAH.

11:59.540 --> 12:00.711
- THAT'S ON THE HOUSE.
OKAY.

12:00.750 --> 12:02.024
- OH, SWEET.
- ENJOY THAT. YEAH.

12:02.060 --> 12:03.368
- OOH.

12:03.410 --> 12:05.162
[bottle clatters]

12:05.200 --> 12:06.508
- SO...
- HI.

12:06.550 --> 12:07.994
OKAY, SO I, UM...

12:08.030 --> 12:09.827
I JUST SENSE
THAT THERE'S THIS CONNECTION,

12:09.860 --> 12:13.580
EVEN THOUGH, YOU KNOW, I...

12:13.620 --> 12:14.655
WHATEVER.

12:14.690 --> 12:17.102
- FALL ASLEEP WHEN YOU TRY
TO COUNT TO MY AGE?

12:17.150 --> 12:18.629
- [laughs]

12:18.660 --> 12:20.355
NO, NO,
DESPITE THAT,

12:20.390 --> 12:23.689
UM, I...

12:23.740 --> 12:24.638
TEACH YOUR DAUGHTER.

12:24.670 --> 12:25.830
- I HAVE A DAUGHTER?

12:25.880 --> 12:27.324
- [laughs]

12:27.360 --> 12:28.975
UM...

12:29.020 --> 12:32.126
SO I-I-I WANTED
TO GIVE YOU THIS.

12:32.160 --> 12:35.744
AND I KNOW THAT TEXTING
IS THE THING

12:35.780 --> 12:37.919
THAT MOST OF THE KIDS
ARE DOING NOWADAYS,

12:37.960 --> 12:39.814
BUT I THINK THERE'S
SOMETHING MORE ROMANTIC

12:39.860 --> 12:41.999
ABOUT, UM, PEN AND PAPER.

12:42.030 --> 12:44.919
UH, BUT DON'T OPEN IT
RIGHT NOW.

12:44.970 --> 12:46.653
UH, I'M GONNA GO.

12:46.690 --> 12:50.103
- OKAY.
- AND, UH, YEAH.

12:50.140 --> 12:53.212
IT WAS NICE TO SEE YOU.
AND JUST FOLLOW THE DIRECTIONS.

12:53.250 --> 12:56.663
- ALL RIGHT, TEACH.
- ALL--[|aughs] ALL RIGHT.

12:56.700 --> 12:58.668
- I AM GONNA G0.
I LIKE YOUR SEAHORSE.

12:58.700 --> 13:01.396
- THANKS.
NICE TO "SEE HORSE" YOU.

13:01.430 --> 13:04.775
- [laughs]
- HEY, SARAH?

13:04.810 --> 13:06.698
- OKAY.
- YOU FORGOT THE ICE.

13:06.750 --> 13:08.058
- OH, YEAH?

13:16.830 --> 13:18.855
ICE, ICE.

13:24.660 --> 13:26.389
- YOU'RE ASKING
FOR MY ADVICE?

13:26.420 --> 13:28.900
- IT'S TRUE.
- WOW, THIS IS SO GREAT.

13:28.940 --> 13:31.625
- [muffled] I KNOW.
- YOU NEVER COME TO ME.

13:31.670 --> 13:33.638
- WELL, YOU KNOW...
- OH.

13:33.670 --> 13:35.149
- THERE'S A FIRST
FOR EVERYTHING.

13:35.190 --> 13:37.329
WHAT'S NEXT?
YOU ASKING ME FOR ADVICE?

13:37.360 --> 13:38.668
- YEAH, MAYBE.

13:38.710 --> 13:40.223
OH, SORRY, GO.
WHAT IS IT?

13:40.260 --> 13:41.602
- I MET SOMEONE.

13:41.640 --> 13:42.743
- UH-HUH.

13:42.780 --> 13:44.816
- AND, UM...

13:44.850 --> 13:46.715
HE'S, UH--HE'S GREAT.

13:46.750 --> 13:48.570
HE'S AMBER'S TEACHER,

13:48.620 --> 13:51.612
AND, UM, HE'S KIND OF YOUNG.

13:51.650 --> 13:52.582
- IS HE LEGAL?

13:52.620 --> 13:54.440
- AGE?
- YEAH.

13:54.480 --> 13:57.062
- YEAH.
HE'S 26.

13:57.110 --> 13:58.657
GROSS.
- OH, OKAY.

13:58.690 --> 14:00.203
OH, HE'S MARRIED.

14:00.250 --> 14:01.694
- WHAT? NO.

14:01.730 --> 14:02.970
- THEN WHAT ARE YOU
ASKING ME ABOUT?

14:03.010 --> 14:04.693
YOU'RE--YOU'RE ALL SYSTEMS GO.
IS THAT IT?

14:06.600 --> 14:08.739
WHAT ABOUT AMBER?
THE GUY'S YOUNGER THAN JULIA.

14:08.770 --> 14:10.874
HE'S YOUNGER THAN ME
BY A LOT.

14:10.910 --> 14:13.492
- LOOK...

14:13.540 --> 14:15.770
YOU WANT TO SAY YES.
- I DO?

14:15.820 --> 14:17.128
- THAT'S WHY
YOU'RE ASKING ME.

14:17.160 --> 14:18.741
IF YOU WANTED TO SAY NO,

14:18.780 --> 14:20.532
YOU'D ASK DUDLEY DO-RIGHT
OR JUDGE JULIA.

14:20.580 --> 14:22.571
- YOU DON'T THINK IT'S WEIRD?
- NO WAY.

14:22.620 --> 14:24.645
- NO RULES.
- NO.

14:24.690 --> 14:26.544
- HA.
- I DIDN'T READ A RULEBOOK.

14:26.580 --> 14:27.615
- THANK YOU SO MUCH.

14:27.650 --> 14:28.719
- YEAH.
- I FEEL MUCH BETTER.

14:28.760 --> 14:30.034
- HEY, THIS WENT
PRETI'Y GOOD, HUH?

14:30.070 --> 14:31.651
- I KNOW.
- RIGHT?

14:31.690 --> 14:32.793
FOR A TRIAL RUN?
- PRETI'Y GOOD.

14:32.830 --> 14:34.479
MAYBE I'LL START ASKING YOU
FOR ALL KINDS OF ADVICE.

14:34.520 --> 14:36.693
- SO, YOU KNOW,
ANYTIME YOU WANT ADVICE...

14:36.730 --> 14:38.698
- OH, REALLY?
ALL RIGHT. OKAY.

14:38.730 --> 14:40.834
YEAH.
- AND JUST, YOU KNOW,

14:40.880 --> 14:42.427
MAYBE TO MAKE IT EVEN,

14:42.460 --> 14:43.768
I'M JUST THROWING THIS
OUT THERE,

14:43.810 --> 14:45.459
BUT WHAT IF YOU CAME WITH ME

14:45.500 --> 14:47.559
TO TELL MOM AND DAD
ABOUT JABBAR?

14:47.610 --> 14:49.430
- WHAT?
NO.

14:49.470 --> 14:51.745
- WAIT, THEN YOU OWE ME ONE,
SOMETHING ELSE.

14:51.780 --> 14:52.883
THINK ABOUT IT.
- OKAY.

14:52.920 --> 14:54.535
- OKAY.
- THANKS FOR YOUR ADVICE.

14:54.580 --> 14:56.434
TELL THEM YOURSELF, YOU FREAK.
- GREAT. YEAH.

14:56.480 --> 14:58.300
- THE STANDARD-ISSUE GUN
IN THE MILITARY

14:58.340 --> 14:59.614
IS THE M4A1.

14:59.650 --> 15:02.585
NOW, THAT'S ONE OF THE MOST
FAMOUS ASSAULT RIFLES THERE IS.

15:02.620 --> 15:03.962
- THIS IS--
THIS IS GREAT.

15:04.000 --> 15:06.104
I CANCELED A MEETING
TO FIND OUT

15:06.140 --> 15:08.381
THAT WE'RE PAYING $30 AN HOUR
FOR A BABYSITI'ER.

15:08.420 --> 15:10.274
THIS IS COSTING US
A LOT OF MONEY, KRISTINA.

15:10.320 --> 15:11.275
- I KNOW. I UNDERSTAND.
- THAT'S ALL.

15:11.320 --> 15:12.867
I JUST WANT TO SEE SOME RESULTS,
THAT'S ALL.

15:12.910 --> 15:13.865
- WELL, DO YOU HAVE A GUN?

15:13.910 --> 15:15.525
- I DO NOT HAVE A GUN, MAX.

15:15.560 --> 15:17.767
- WELL, IF YOU WERE GONNA GET
A GUN, THE--THE AK-47 IS...

15:17.810 --> 15:19.778
- THIS IS GREAT.

15:19.810 --> 15:22.256
SHE'S PLAYING BALL WITH HIM
AND LOOKING UP THE HILL.

15:22.300 --> 15:24.393
- HEY, MAX, IT LOOKS
LIKE THAT GIRL OVER THERE

15:24.440 --> 15:25.702
WANTS TO PLAY
SOME FOUR SQUARE--

15:25.750 --> 15:27.468
OVER THERE BY THE TREE.
- WHY?

15:27.510 --> 15:29.535
- WHY DON'T YOU GO ASK HER
IF SHE WANTS TO PLAY?

15:29.580 --> 15:30.547
- I'LL JUST PLAY WITH YOU.

15:30.580 --> 15:32.719
- ACTUALLY...
- I'LL JUST PLAY WITH YOU.

15:32.750 --> 15:33.853
- NO.
- [scoffs]

15:33.890 --> 15:35.266
- SHE'S GONNA TRY TO GET HIM
TO PLAY WITH THAT KID...

15:35.310 --> 15:36.538
- RIGHT.
- THAT GIRL BY THE TREE.

15:36.590 --> 15:37.921
- GOOD LUCK.
- YEAH.

15:37.970 --> 15:39.483
A BLIZZARD'S COMING IN
LATER TODAY TOO.

15:39.520 --> 15:40.964
- MM-HMM. RIGHT.
- AND YOU GET A LIZARD

15:41.000 --> 15:43.582
ON THE WAY HOME.
- WHAT KIND OF LIZARD?

15:43.630 --> 15:44.938
- ANY LIZARD YOU WANT.

15:44.970 --> 15:48.007
- OKAY.

15:48.050 --> 15:50.143
- YOU KNOW HOW MANY TIMES
I'VE TRIED THIS?

15:50.190 --> 15:52.499
- NOW, REMEMBER, LOOK HER
IN THE EYE, OKAY?

15:52.530 --> 15:54.839
AND DON'T FORGET
TO GIVE HER A SMILE.

15:54.880 --> 15:56.495
- HI, I'M MAX.

15:56.540 --> 15:58.599
- I'M JESSICA.

15:59.880 --> 16:02.644
- HUH.

16:02.680 --> 16:04.910
- OH, UH, DO YOU WANT
TO PLAY FOUR SQUARE?

16:04.960 --> 16:07.929
- SURE.

16:07.960 --> 16:09.575
- [softly] I DID IT.
- YOU'LL GET IT.

16:09.620 --> 16:11.588
- [whispers]
- YOU'LL GET YOUR LIZARD.

16:15.690 --> 16:18.318
- WELL, HOW ABOUT THAT?

16:25.430 --> 16:29.639
HEY, YOU KNOW,
SHE JUST GOT LUCKY.

16:29.670 --> 16:31.877
- NO, SHE DIDN'T.

16:31.920 --> 16:33.706
- SWEETIE...

16:33.750 --> 16:35.672
HEY.

16:38.410 --> 16:40.128
- [roars]

16:40.170 --> 16:41.740
[kids screaming]

16:41.790 --> 16:43.508
THE DRAGON IS HUNGRY!

16:43.550 --> 16:45.643
[growling and shrieking]

16:45.690 --> 16:47.658
- ISN'T HE AMAZING?

16:47.690 --> 16:50.443
ALL KIDS SHOULD HAVE
A MALE ROLE MODEL LIKE JOEL.

16:50.490 --> 16:52.936
- YEAH, HE'S REALLY GREAT
WITH THEM, HUH?

16:52.970 --> 16:54.619
- IT'S A GIFT.

16:54.660 --> 16:56.412
- HE'S LIKE A ROCK STAR.

16:56.460 --> 16:59.759
- BIG-TIME.

16:59.810 --> 17:01.664
- UH-OH, UH-OH, UH-OH.

17:01.710 --> 17:03.280
IT LOOKS LIKE THE PRINCESS

17:03.330 --> 17:04.774
HAS SOME ANTS ON A LOG
FOR ALL OF YOU.

17:04.810 --> 17:06.391
- LOOK WHAT JOEL MADE,
EVERYBODY.

17:06.430 --> 17:09.126
- WHO WANTS SOME OF THOSE?
[kids cheering]

17:09.160 --> 17:10.468
- OKAY.
- THERE THEY ARE.

17:10.510 --> 17:12.978
- OKAY. YOU WANNA DO THAT?
- OH, ABSOLUTELY.

17:13.030 --> 17:15.646
- DO YOU NEED ANYTHING?
- I'M GOOD, I'M GOOD.

17:15.680 --> 17:17.409
- OH, LOOK AT THIS.

17:17.450 --> 17:19.543
SHE'S THE PRESIDENT
OF HIS FAN CLUB HERE.

17:19.590 --> 17:21.205
- YOU OKAY? YOU OKAY?
- I THINK SO.

17:26.760 --> 17:28.148
- [laughs]

17:28.180 --> 17:30.171
HE'S HAVING A BALL.
- MM-HMM.

17:30.220 --> 17:32.381
- I JUST--I DON'T KNOW
HOW YOU DID IT.

17:32.430 --> 17:35.729
I MEAN, I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO DO THIS FOR SO LONG,

17:35.770 --> 17:37.419
AND I'M...

17:37.470 --> 17:39.563
I'M JUST AMAZED.

17:39.610 --> 17:42.181
DO YOU WANT A SNACK--
AN APPLE OR SOMETHING?

17:42.230 --> 17:43.913
I HAVE TONS.
- HOW ARE YOU?

17:43.950 --> 17:46.123
- HOW AM I?
- HOW ARE YOU--

17:46.160 --> 17:48.025
YEAH, HOW ARE YOU DOING?
- I'M GOOD.

17:48.060 --> 17:51.336
- BUT I MEAN, LIKE...
- I'M GOOD, I PROMISE.

17:52.960 --> 17:55.895
IT'S JUST SO NICE TO SEE MAX
PLAY WITH OTHER KIDS, YOU KNOW.

17:55.930 --> 17:57.409
[clears throat]
- MM-HMM.

17:57.450 --> 17:59.441
- AND YOU HELPED HIM DO IT.
- MM-HMM.

17:59.490 --> 18:01.412
- YOU DID.

18:02.870 --> 18:04.451
- NONE OF THIS IS EASY,
YOU KNOW.

18:04.490 --> 18:06.355
- I'M SORRY.
I JUST FEEL LIKE A LOSER.

18:06.390 --> 18:08.381
I FEEL LIKE A TOTAL LOSER.

18:08.430 --> 18:11.149
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO DO THIS
FOR SO LONG,

18:11.190 --> 18:13.397
AND YOU MAKE IT SEEM
SO EASY.

18:13.430 --> 18:16.638
I MEAN, JUST WATCHING...
- IT'S NOT.

18:16.680 --> 18:20.389
IT'S HARD, AND I ONLY WORK
WITH HIM A FEW HOURS A DAY.

18:20.440 --> 18:22.579
THIS IS YOUR LIFE,
YOU KNOW?

18:22.610 --> 18:24.305
- [sighing]
OH.

18:24.340 --> 18:25.546
- I DON'T KNOW
HOW YOU DO IT.

18:25.580 --> 18:29.129
- I KNOW. I--
WELL, THAT'S WHAT NOBODY GETS.

18:29.170 --> 18:31.309
I TRY TO EXPLAIN...

18:31.350 --> 18:34.376
JUST THE WORRY--
THE WORRY NEVER GOES AWAY.

18:34.420 --> 18:36.866
LIKE, I-I FIND MYSELF
UP LATE AT NIGHT

18:36.900 --> 18:39.175
JUST WORRYING
ABOUT MAX, AND...

18:39.220 --> 18:41.666
IS THERE SOMETHING
WE SHOULD HAVE TRIED?

18:41.700 --> 18:43.349
SOMETHING WE SHOULD TRY?

18:43.390 --> 18:46.279
WHEN I'M NOT WORRIED ABOUT HIM,
I'M WORRIED ABOUT THE FACT

18:46.330 --> 18:47.490
THAT I'M NOT WORRIED
ABOUT HADDIE.

18:47.540 --> 18:49.223
AND WHEN I'M NOT WORRIED
ABOUT HADDIE--

18:49.260 --> 18:51.364
IT'S JUST LIKE IT NEVER STOPS,
YOU KNOW?

18:51.400 --> 18:53.539
ADAM AND I--
MAYBE WE GET A-A CHANCE

18:53.580 --> 18:55.844
TO SPEND SOME TIME ALONE,
JUST TOGETHER...

18:55.890 --> 18:57.573
- YEAH.
- SOME MIRACLE CHANCE.

18:57.610 --> 19:00.090
IT'S LIKE I CANNOT STOP
WORRYING LONG ENOUGH

19:00.130 --> 19:01.757
TO ENJOY ANYTHING--

19:01.790 --> 19:03.587
ANYTHING, LIKE A MOVIE

19:03.620 --> 19:05.759
OR A NICE DINNER
OR SEX, IF...

19:05.790 --> 19:08.554
OH, MY GOD, I'M SORRY.
I SHOULDN'T--

19:08.590 --> 19:10.444
- NO, NO, NO, NO.
- I'M SO SORRY.

19:10.490 --> 19:12.412
- IT'S OKAY.
- DON'T TELL HIM I SAID THAT.

19:12.460 --> 19:15.145
- I WON'T.
- 'CAUSE HE DOES SATISFY ME...

19:15.180 --> 19:16.977
- I'M SURE HE DOES.
- A LOT.

19:17.010 --> 19:18.216
HE'S GOT A GOOD ONE.

19:18.260 --> 19:20.979
[both laughing]

19:21.020 --> 19:23.113
OKAY.

19:23.160 --> 19:24.388
NEVER MIND.

19:24.430 --> 19:26.910
- LISTEN, YOU NEED TO RELAX.

19:26.950 --> 19:28.121
- OH, MY GOD.

19:28.160 --> 19:30.640
- HONESTLY, YOU'RE TOO HARD
ON YOURSELF.

19:30.680 --> 19:34.639
YOU NEED TO JUST CUT YOURSELF
SOME SLACK AND RELAX.

19:34.690 --> 19:35.679
- OKAY.

19:35.720 --> 19:38.336
OKAY, THEN I'M GONNA GO
TO HAWAII,

19:38.380 --> 19:39.608
AND YOU CAN RAISE
MY SON.

19:39.660 --> 19:41.548
- I'LL BABYSIT.
HOW ABOUT THAT?

19:48.770 --> 19:49.691
- YEAH, I DON'T THINK

19:49.740 --> 19:50.809
THAT THEY'RE GONNA SPRING
ANYTHING ON YOU.

19:50.840 --> 19:52.808
THE DEPOSITION IS NOW SET
FOR THURSDAY MORNING.

19:52.840 --> 19:56.150
AND, UM, WE'RE GONNA GO OVER
ALL OF IT

19:56.190 --> 19:57.157
AT THE BRIEFING
BEFOREHAND.

19:57.190 --> 19:58.009
- THANK YOU.
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

19:58.050 --> 19:59.631
CAN--CAN I CALL YOU BACK
ABOUT THIS?

19:59.680 --> 20:01.056
JUST GIVE ME A COUPLE MINUTES.

20:01.090 --> 20:02.398
SOMETHING HAS COME UP
IN THE FAMILY.

20:02.440 --> 20:05.364
I-I WILL CALL YOU
RIGHT BACK.

20:06.170 --> 20:07.569
- THANK YOU.

20:07.620 --> 20:08.302
- FOR WHAT?

20:08.340 --> 20:09.307
- THE PLAYGROUP...

20:09.340 --> 20:11.262
- YEAH?
- WAS INSPIRATIONAL.

20:11.310 --> 20:12.959
I MEAN, WOW.

20:13.000 --> 20:15.036
YOUR HUSBAND IS A ROCK STAR.

20:15.070 --> 20:16.651
- HE IS, ISN'T HE?

20:16.690 --> 20:17.896
- OH!

20:17.940 --> 20:19.862
I MEAN,
NO DISRESPECT TO DAD,

20:22.460 --> 20:24.519
YOU KNOW, SOMEONE I WANT
TO BE LIKE AS A DAD.

20:24.560 --> 20:27.734
- OH, MY GOD.
ADAM'S A GOOD DAD.

20:27.770 --> 20:31.115
- WELL, YEAH, HE'S A GREAT DAD,
BUT HE'S NOT A ROCK STAR.

20:31.160 --> 20:32.252
JOEL...

20:32.300 --> 20:33.915
ON THE OTHER HAND, WOW.

20:33.950 --> 20:35.531
- WAIT, OKAY,
WHAT DO YOU MEAN BY ROCK STAR?

20:35.570 --> 20:36.673
- WELL, HE'S WORSHIPPED.

20:36.710 --> 20:38.814
- OH, YEAH.
- LIKE A DEITY.

20:38.850 --> 20:40.363
- YEAH, THE KIDS LOVE HIM.

20:40.410 --> 20:42.401
- WELL, NOT JUST THE KIDS,
BELIEVE ME.

20:42.440 --> 20:43.850
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

20:45.620 --> 20:46.689
- NOTHING.

20:46.720 --> 20:48.995
- NO, NO, YOU SAID "WORSHIPPED."
WHO WORSHIPS HIM?

20:49.040 --> 20:51.133
- YOU KNOW, THE, UM...

20:51.180 --> 20:52.727
TH E--TH E KIDS

20:52.760 --> 20:54.489
AND--AND THE TWO GAY DADS,
TIMMY AND TONY,

20:54.520 --> 20:56.795
OR WHATEVER, AND ME.
- YEAH.

20:56.840 --> 20:58.489
- AND THE OTHER MOMS.
- WHICH OTHER MOMS?

20:58.530 --> 21:00.350
- ALL THE OTHER MOMS.
- ALL THE OTHER MOMS?

21:00.390 --> 21:01.948
- WELL, NO, NOT ALL OF THEM.

21:01.980 --> 21:04.016
- RACQUEL?
IS IT RACQUEL?

21:04.050 --> 21:04.948
- I REALLY COULDN'T SAY.

21:04.980 --> 21:06.424
- OH, YOU'RE SUCH A BAD LIAR.

21:06.470 --> 21:08.461
- I KNOW.
[laughs]

21:08.500 --> 21:10.843
- SO--SO COME ON.
- LISTEN.

21:10.890 --> 21:13.085
- SO--SO WHAT IS SHE LIKE
WHEN I'M NOT AROUND?

21:13.130 --> 21:15.018
_ 1--
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW.

21:16.930 --> 21:17.954
- DOES SHE FLIRT?

