WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

31:43.410 --> 31:46.038
- IT'S EXTRA CREDIT
FOR SCHOOL, OKAY?

31:46.070 --> 31:48.823
MR. CYR, MY ENGLISH TEACHER.
- OH. FOR MR. CYR?

31:48.870 --> 31:50.826
- YEAH.
- OH, THAT'S GREAT.

31:50.870 --> 31:52.383
- YEAH.
- EXTRA CREDIT, THAT'S GOOD.

31:52.420 --> 31:53.796
- YEAH, NO BIG DEAL.
- NO, I KNOW.

31:53.840 --> 31:56.422
I'M JUST--I'M...

31:56.460 --> 31:57.381
I-I-I'M PROUD OF YOU.

31:57.430 --> 31:59.807
YOU KNOW, EXTRA CREDIT,
THAT'S EXTRA.

31:59.840 --> 32:01.467
- OKAY.
- YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THAT.

32:01.500 --> 32:04.469
- DON'T BE WEIRD.
- I'M NOT WEIRD.

32:23.250 --> 32:25.514
- LITTLE SCOOP OF ICE CREAM.
- RIGHT.

32:25.560 --> 32:27.903
- YOU KNOW, LIKE...
- YOU WANT IT 50/50.

32:27.940 --> 32:29.623
- AT LEAST 50/50.
- YEAH, YEAH.

32:29.670 --> 32:31.490
MAYBE EVEN MORE ICE CREAM.

32:31.530 --> 32:32.667
- PRETTY GOOD.
- HEY, THIS IS ON ME.

32:32.700 --> 32:34.019
- HUH?

32:34.050 --> 32:36.154
- I GOT--I GOT THIS.
I GOT THIS ONE.

32:36.190 --> 32:37.805
- THAT'S UNPRECEDENTED.

32:37.850 --> 32:39.249
- IT'S MY WAY
OF SAYING THANK YOU

32:39.300 --> 32:41.120
FOR ALL THE NICE THINGS
YOU GUYS DO FOR ME.

32:41.160 --> 32:42.468
- THAT'S VERY SWEET OF YOU.

32:42.510 --> 32:45.786
- OH, MAN,
THIS IS EMBARRASSING.

32:45.820 --> 32:48.300
CAN YOU FLOAT ME 40...
DAD, DAD.

32:48.340 --> 32:50.615
I'M KIDDING. I'M--I'M KIDDING.
- REALLY?

32:50.650 --> 32:52.402
- YEAH, I HAVE IT.

32:52.450 --> 32:55.681
LISTEN, YOU KNOW, THE--THE
CARE PACKAGES AND THE LAUNDRY

32:55.730 --> 32:58.381
AND THE BOAT REPAIRS, I KNOW
YOU THINK I TAKE IT FOR GRANTED,

32:58.420 --> 33:00.479
BUT I DON'T.
I APPRECIATE IT.

33:00.530 --> 33:02.248
I REALLY DO.

33:05.560 --> 33:06.629
- YOU FEELING OKAY?

33:06.670 --> 33:08.592
- YEAH.
I FEEL GREAT.

33:08.640 --> 33:11.564
I ALSO WANT TO SAY
THAT I'M NOT GONNA BE

33:11.610 --> 33:13.259
SUCH A BURDEN ANYMORE
TO YOUR GUYS.

33:13.300 --> 33:17.054
- WELL, I WOULDN'T SAY
YOU'VE BEEN A BURDEN.

33:17.090 --> 33:19.331
- DEFINE BURDEN.

33:19.370 --> 33:20.951
- I'VE BEEN WORKING MORE HOURS,

33:20.990 --> 33:23.026
AND I'VE BEEN--I'VE BEEN
PUTTING AWAY SOME CASH.

33:23.070 --> 33:25.641
I'M PREPARING FOR, UH...

33:25.690 --> 33:27.203
THE NEXT STAGE IN MY LIFE.

33:27.240 --> 33:29.800
- CROSBY, YOU'RE STARTING
TO SCARE THE HELL OUT OF ME.

33:29.830 --> 33:31.343
- US, ACTUALLY.

33:31.380 --> 33:33.439
- IT'S NOT BAD.
IT'S A--IT'S A GOOD THING.

33:33.490 --> 33:36.653
IT'S--IT'S
A REALLY GOOD THING.

33:36.700 --> 33:40.591
YOU KNOW, PEOPLE WOULD SAY
IT'S A GREAT THING.

33:40.630 --> 33:43.667
UH, I HAVE A SON.

33:43.710 --> 33:47.840
- YOU WHAT?
- I'M A FATHER.

33:47.880 --> 33:52.396
- SO YOU AND CRAZY KATIE HIT
THE JACKPOT, THEN, RIGHT?

33:52.440 --> 33:54.431
- NO, NO, IT'S NOT--
IT'S NOT CRAZY KATIE,

33:54.480 --> 33:56.095
AND YOU
SHOULDN'T CALL HER THAT.

33:56.130 --> 33:58.473
THAT'S A LITTLE ROUGH.
- WELL, YOU CALL HER THAT.

33:58.510 --> 34:00.580
- IT'S ANOTHER WOMAN
FROM A FEW YEARS AGO

34:00.620 --> 34:02.542
WHO'S A DANCER,

34:02.590 --> 34:04.649
AND SHE WAS TOURING
THE BAY AREA,

34:04.690 --> 34:08.035
AND WE HAD SOME FUN.

34:08.080 --> 34:09.763
AND YOU KNOW HOW I FEEL
ABOUT DANCERS.

34:09.800 --> 34:11.449
- SHE'S AN EXOTIC--
- NO, SHE DOESN'T DANCE

34:11.490 --> 34:14.288
WITH A POLE.
SHE'S LIKE--YOU KNOW, BALLET.

34:14.320 --> 34:17.289
ANYWAYS, LOOK, I DIDN'T KNOW
SHE GOT PREGNANT.

34:17.330 --> 34:20.458
AND THEN SHE SHOWED UP
A FEW MONTHS AGO WITH A BOY.

34:20.500 --> 34:23.321
UH, HE--
HE'S FIVE YEARS OLD.

34:29.130 --> 34:31.473
- AND YOU--
YOU'RE SERIOUS?

34:31.510 --> 34:34.138
- YEAH. YES.
- YOU'RE SURE HE'S YOURS?

34:34.170 --> 34:36.092
I MEAN, YOU'VE HAD THE TEST
AND EVERYTHING?

34:36.140 --> 34:37.755
- YEAH, I'M SURE HE'S MINE.

34:37.790 --> 34:40.350
HE'S, UM--HE'S AMAZING.

34:40.380 --> 34:42.655
I MEAN, YOU'RE--
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE HIM.

34:42.700 --> 34:46.101
HE'S REALLY GREAT.

34:46.150 --> 34:48.903
- CROSBY...

34:48.940 --> 34:50.908
YOU'RE A DAD.
- YEAH.

34:50.950 --> 34:52.429
I KNOW IT'S--IT'S CRAZY,

34:52.460 --> 34:55.497
BUT, UH, I'M REALLY TAKING
THIS THING SERIOUSLY.

34:55.540 --> 34:58.088
THAT'S WHAT I MEANT
ABOUT A NEW STAGE IN MY LIFE.

34:58.130 --> 34:59.745
LIKE, I--
THIS IS ME NOW--

34:59.780 --> 35:01.190
CROSBY, THE DAD.

35:01.230 --> 35:03.744
AND I'M GONNA BE MORE
RESPONSIBLE AND INDEPENDENT.

35:03.790 --> 35:06.748
MOM, PLEASE SAY SOMETHING.

35:06.790 --> 35:10.089
YOU LOOK LIKE YOU'RE GONNA...
- DOES HE LOOK LIKE YOU?

35:10.140 --> 35:12.301
'CAUSE YOU WERE
JUST THE CUTEST KID EVER.

35:12.350 --> 35:15.865
- HE--HE LOOKS--
YEAH, HE LOOKS LIKE ME.

35:15.900 --> 35:18.528
- I'M JUST SO HAPPY
FOR YOU,

35:18.560 --> 35:20.346
FOR ALL OF US.

35:20.390 --> 35:23.143
WHEN DO WE GET
TO MEET HIM?

35:23.190 --> 35:24.384
- I'LL ASK HIS MOM
WHEN HE HAS SOME FREE TIME.

35:24.430 --> 35:26.113
- WHAT'S HIS NAME?
- JABBAR.

35:26.150 --> 35:28.732
- JABB--JABBAR?

35:28.780 --> 35:30.498
- YEAH, JABBAR.
- JABBAR.

35:30.540 --> 35:32.087
- JABBAR.
- WHAT KIND OF NAME IS JABBAR?

35:32.130 --> 35:33.677
- WHAT THE HELL KIND OF NAME
IS ZEEK?

35:33.710 --> 35:35.359
- IT DOESN'T MATTER--
THE NAME DOESN'T MATTER.

35:35.400 --> 35:36.981
- WHAT'S HIS LAST NAME?
IS IT BRAVERMAN?

35:37.030 --> 35:38.748
IT BETTER BE BRAVERMAN.

35:38.790 --> 35:40.234
JABBAR BRAVERMAN?

35:40.270 --> 35:43.307
- I'M WORKING ON THAT.
- [laughs]

35:43.340 --> 35:44.375
- WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

35:44.410 --> 35:46.822
- YOU'RE A DADDY.

35:46.860 --> 35:49.420
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.
- I KNOW. ME NEITHER.

35:49.450 --> 35:52.624
[adding machine whirs]

35:59.570 --> 36:01.879
- HEY.

36:01.910 --> 36:03.047
- HI.

36:03.090 --> 36:05.490
- UM...
- HEY.

36:05.540 --> 36:08.885
- HI. I-I-I WAS JUST--I'VE BEEN
THINKING ABOUT THE NOTE.

36:08.920 --> 36:10.774
- I KNOW.
I'M SORRY.

36:10.820 --> 36:12.196
- NO NEED TO APOLOGIZE.

36:12.230 --> 36:13.606
I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

36:13.650 --> 36:17.404
MAYBE IT WAS A LITTLE...
TOO COMPLICATED.

36:17.450 --> 36:20.578
I MEAN, THREE OPTIONS IS A LOT
OF OPTIONS.

36:20.620 --> 36:22.201
THAT'S...

36:22.240 --> 36:24.800
THAT'S OVERWHELMING.

36:24.830 --> 36:26.138
I UNDERSTAND.
- YEAH.

36:26.180 --> 36:30.287
I'M JUST NOT GOOD
WITH MULTIPLE CHOICE.

36:30.320 --> 36:32.424
- NO, NO, NO,
THIS IS--THIS IS MY FAULT.

36:32.460 --> 36:34.428
I MEAN, THESE CHOICES
ARE RIDICULOUS.

36:34.460 --> 36:36.325
MAYBE--
WHAT THE HELL'S THAT?

36:36.360 --> 36:37.907
THAT'S NOT A REAL CHOICE.

36:37.950 --> 36:39.156
- CONFUSING.

36:39.190 --> 36:40.361
- I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I WAS THINKING.

36:40.400 --> 36:41.606
I WAS JUST TRYING
TO WRITE SOMETHING.

36:41.640 --> 36:46.339
SO I WAS THINKING THAT I SHOULD
JUST BE MORE DIRECT, UM...

36:46.370 --> 36:48.338
NEXT TIME.
- HMM.

36:56.310 --> 37:00.588
- FRIENDS TELL ME
IT'S SPRING

37:00.630 --> 37:03.098
MY WINDOW SHOWS THE SAME

37:03.150 --> 37:07.109
- WILL YOU GO OUT WITH ME?

37:07.150 --> 37:08.356
- WITHOUT YOU HERE

37:08.390 --> 37:12.633
THE SEASONS PASS ME BY

37:16.990 --> 37:20.608
I KNOW YOU WERE NOT KNOWN

37:23.480 --> 37:26.301
- THAT IS THE CORRECT ANSWER.

37:28.380 --> 37:33.443
OKAY, I-I WON'T INTERRUPT
YOU ANYMORE.

37:33.490 --> 37:35.549
- TODAY HAS BEEN OKAY

37:37.940 --> 37:41.319
TODAY HAS BEEN OKAY

37:49.430 --> 37:52.228
- YOU READY, BUDDY?
- YEAH. LET'S GO. LET'S GO.

37:52.270 --> 37:54.261
[car door closes]

37:55.130 --> 37:57.052
- HEY, GUYS.
- OH, THEY'RE HERE.

37:57.100 --> 37:58.715
- HEY.

37:58.750 --> 38:00.377
- WE'RE HERE.

38:08.040 --> 38:10.554
- OH, WOW.
- THIS IS JABBAR.

38:10.590 --> 38:14.071
- JABBAR.
- HI, MR. AND MRS. BRAVERMAN.

38:14.110 --> 38:17.045
- OH.
- [laughs]

38:17.080 --> 38:19.184
- HE HAS YOUR SMILE.

38:19.220 --> 38:22.109
- THIS IS GRAH'IDMA CAMILLE.

38:22.160 --> 38:24.469
- HELLO, JABBAR.
- AND THAT TALL SUCKER

38:24.500 --> 38:26.252
IS GRANDPA ZEEK.
- JABBAR, HOW ARE YOU?

38:26.300 --> 38:28.985
HEY, YOU GOT A GOOD HANDSHAKE.
- HI. [chuckles]

38:29.030 --> 38:30.156
- YOU CAN CALL ME GRANDMA.

38:30.200 --> 38:33.089
- OKAY.
- COME HERE. YOU HUNGRY?

38:33.130 --> 38:36.782
WE'RE BARBECUING.

38:36.830 --> 38:39.515
WE'RE GONNA GRILL
SOME CHICKEN.

38:41.870 --> 38:43.758
- WHAT DO YOU THINK?
- OH, BOY.

38:43.800 --> 38:45.381
IT'S REALLY HARD
TO PUT IT INTO WORDS.

38:45.420 --> 38:46.648
- YEAH, I BET.
I BET.

38:46.700 --> 38:48.975
[deep voice] WOULD YOU MIND
IF I BORROWED YOUR TOOTHBRUSH?

38:49.010 --> 38:51.114
[high-pitched voice] WHY?
WHY DO YOU NEED MY TOOTHBRUSH?

38:51.150 --> 38:53.596
[deep voice] OH, I RAN
OUT OF EGGS THIS MORNING,

38:53.640 --> 38:54.948
SO I ATE MY GYM SOCK.

38:54.980 --> 38:55.799
[laughter]

38:55.850 --> 38:57.989
[high-pitched voice]
YOUR GYM SOCK?

38:58.020 --> 38:59.294
- THAT'S AMAZING.

38:59.330 --> 39:03.266
- HE LOOKS SO GROWN-UP.

39:03.300 --> 39:05.291
- YEAH.
WHO'D HAVE THOUGHT?

39:05.340 --> 39:06.819
- [deep voice]
I GOT IT FROM MY GRANDPA.

39:06.860 --> 39:08.122
[high-pitched voice]
WELL, WHO'S THAT?

39:08.170 --> 39:09.091
[deep voice]
ORVILLE REDENSOCKER'S.

39:09.130 --> 39:11.644
[laughter]
[high-pitched voice] WHOOPSIES.

39:11.690 --> 39:13.339
NOW, IF YOU DON'T EAT POPCORN,
WHAT DO YOU EAT?

39:13.380 --> 39:16.964
[deep voice] I LIKE THE SOFI'ER
FOODS--PEARS, PLUMS, TOOTHPASTE.

39:17.000 --> 39:18.444
[high-pitched voice] TOOTHPASTE?
WHO EATS TOOTH PASTE?

39:18.490 --> 39:20.037
[deep voice]
ALL THE PEOPLE WITH GREAT BREATH

39:20.080 --> 39:22.287
ARE EATING TOOTHPASTE.
- THIS IS AMAZING.

39:22.320 --> 39:23.969
OH, WOULD YOU LOOK AT THAT?

39:24.010 --> 39:25.625
DOES THAT JUST MELT
YOUR HEART OR WHAT?

39:25.670 --> 39:27.979
YOU KNOW, I WAS THINKING
OF SIGNING HARMONY UP

39:28.020 --> 39:28.805
FOR A POTTERY CLASS.

39:28.840 --> 39:30.182
YOU KNOW,
WORKING WITH THE CLAY,

39:30.220 --> 39:33.940
IT JUST GROUNDS YOU
TO THE EARTH.

39:33.990 --> 39:36.436
- [deep voice]
THEY'RE NOT HARD TO GET.

39:36.470 --> 39:38.085
[high-pitched voice]
THERE'S NO CREDIT CHECK?

39:38.130 --> 39:42.476
[light laughter]

39:42.510 --> 39:44.091
- MAYBE THE GIRLS
CAN DO IT TOGETHER.

39:44.140 --> 39:45.368
- OH, HARMONY
WOULD LOVE THAT.

39:45.410 --> 39:46.684
- YEAH, I'M SURE
SYDNEY WOULD TOO.

39:46.720 --> 39:49.826
- [deep voice] ASK ME TO LEAVE
BEFORE THE TICKLING GOT GOING.

39:49.870 --> 39:51.519
[high-pitched voice]
YEAH, WE DIDN'T LIKE YOUR LOOK.

39:51.560 --> 39:52.959
I GUESS
I SHOULDN'T HAVE JUDGED YOU

39:53.010 --> 39:55.524
JUST BASED
ON YOUR INCREDIBLY RED MOUTH

39:55.560 --> 39:57.141
AND GIGANTIC EYEBROW.

39:57.180 --> 39:58.829
[laughter]

39:58.870 --> 40:02.044
- MY NAME IS...
- OKAY, CLOSE YOUR EYES.

40:02.080 --> 40:03.183
- OH.
- CLOSE YOUR EYES.

40:03.220 --> 40:04.539
- THAT WAS MY MOUTH,
BUT OKAY.

40:04.570 --> 40:05.844
- ALL RIGHT,
OPEN THEM NOW.

40:05.880 --> 40:07.154
TA- DA!

40:07.190 --> 40:09.226
[horn honking]

40:09.260 --> 40:11.012
- HUH?
- OH, YOU STILL HAVE THAT?

40:11.060 --> 40:12.459
- WHOA.
- OH, MAN.

40:12.510 --> 40:15.126
- THAT WAS YOUR DAD'S
WHEN HE WAS YOUR AGE.

40:15.170 --> 40:16.501
- YEAH, COME ON.
- IT'S FOR ME?

40:16.550 --> 40:17.858
- YOU BETCHA.
HOP ON.

40:17.890 --> 40:19.642
- MAYBE YOUR DAD'LL TEACH YOU
SOME TRICKS ON IT.

40:19.690 --> 40:22.409
- YEAH, BUT I DON'T WANT YOU
DOING ANY WHEELIES,

40:22.450 --> 40:24.896
'CAUSE YOUR DAD BROKE THREE
TEETH AND A LOT OF BRAIN CELLS.

40:24.930 --> 40:26.272
- DON'T REMIND ME.

40:26.320 --> 40:28.208
- I GAINED GLORY, THOUGH.

40:28.250 --> 40:29.797
CAN YOU DO THIS?
- YEAH.

40:29.840 --> 40:30.864
- YOU ALREADY KNOW HOW?
- YEAH.

40:30.910 --> 40:32.662
- OKAY.
I'M GONNA HELP YOU OUT

40:32.700 --> 40:34.873
TO THE STREET, ALL RIGHT?
- EASY DOES IT.

40:34.910 --> 40:37.731
- [groans]
- HEY, YOU LOOK GOOD ON THAT.

40:37.780 --> 40:40.089
- GRANDPA, GRANDMA,
YOU WATCHING?

40:40.120 --> 40:42.111
- WE'RE WATCHING.
- OKAY.

40:42.160 --> 40:43.366
- ALL RIGHT, YOU READY?
- YEAH.

40:43.400 --> 40:45.083
- ALL RIGHT, LET'S DO IT.
- WHOO-HOO!

40:45.130 --> 40:46.290
- PEDALING.
- WHOO-HOO!

40:46.340 --> 40:48.956
- COME ON, JABBAR.
- WHOO-HOO!

40:48.990 --> 40:54.098
-AH

40:54.140 --> 40:59.726
AH

40:59.760 --> 41:05.346
AH

41:05.390 --> 41:07.529
[Kristina moans]

41:07.560 --> 41:09.972
HOLY CRAP.

41:10.010 --> 41:12.422
MWAH.
- OH.

41:12.470 --> 41:15.155
[both breathing heavily]

41:15.190 --> 41:19.149
- OH, MY GOD.

41:19.200 --> 41:22.055
- THAT DEFINITELY BEAT THE TIME
AFTER THE DAILY SHOW.

41:22.100 --> 41:23.226
- OH, YEAH.

41:23.270 --> 41:27.991
AND THE TIME AFTER LENO.

41:28.030 --> 41:30.828
[chuckles]

41:30.860 --> 41:32.066
OH, MY GOD.

41:39.180 --> 41:40.761
OH, MAN.

41:50.950 --> 41:54.124
- SO I'M JUST GONNA SAY
THAT FELT LIKE...

41:54.160 --> 41:55.775
THE REAL DEAL.

41:55.820 --> 41:58.641
AM I RIGHT?
- YEAH. YOU'RE RIGHT.

41:58.680 --> 42:01.808
YEP.
YOU ARE RIGHT.

42:03.140 --> 42:06.587
- BUT EVEN IF IT WASN'T,
YOU'D PROBABLY SAY THAT IT WAS.

42:06.620 --> 42:08.827
- BUT IT WAS
THE REAL DEAL, HONEY.

42:08.870 --> 42:10.553
IT WAS.
- DEFINITELY?

42:10.590 --> 42:12.797
- YES. UH-HUH.
- DEFINITELY DEFINITELY?

42:12.840 --> 42:18.005
- UH-HUH. ADAM, I HAVEN'T FELT
THIS RELAXED IN TWO MONTHS.

42:18.600 --> 42:21.114
PLEASE DON'T RUIN IT.

42:23.260 --> 42:26.115
- [sighs]
